    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3091: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>352. Your 419, December 1, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>Assuming that the proposed loan to the Chinese Government for famine relief
                    involves no public flotation of bonds, the Department concurs in the view that
                    it does not come within the provisions of the Consortium Agreement. The
                    Department assumes that Bennett has discussed the matter with the other
                    Consortium representatives and that they concur in this view; and on this
                    condition it offers no objection. You may so advise Bennett.</p>
                <p>Which French bank is referred to in your telegram?</p>
                <p>The Department desires to be informed whether proposed customs surtax has
                    received assent of the Powers and if so when does it become effective?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
